
Launch Kafka docker container using the following command:
 docker run -d --name kafka -p 9092:9092 apache/kafka:latest

This command will pull the latest Apache Kafka image from Docker Hub and run it in a detached mode, mapping port 9092 of the container to port 9092 on your host machine.
You can then connect to Kafka using a Kafka client on your host machine.

Hit the API v1/api/kafka/publishMessage to publish messages to Kafka topic
with payload as UserDetails JSON object.
Example payload:
{
  "userId": "123",
  "firstName": "firstName",
  "lastName": "testName",
  "mobileNumberList": [
    "13141412412",
    "35532434234"
  ],
  "bankAccountDetails": {
    "ICICI": {
      "bankId": "5435234324",
      "bankIFSCNumber": "XXXXXXX",
      "bankAccountNumber": "2324235423",
      "bankUPIId": "653243@ybl"
    }
  }
}
